description:
In tts/mod.rs's generate_audio_from_phonemes, the phoneme-to-token loop has no else branch for unmapped characters:

    for c in phonemes.chars() {
        if let Some(&id) = self.vocab.get(&c) {
            token_ids.push(id);
        }
        // else: silently skipped -- no warning, no error
    }

Any IPA character in a raw --phonemes input that isn't present in the loaded model's tokens.txt just vanishes from the token sequence with zero signal that anything went wrong. This was found while comparing kokoro-rs against moonshine-go's newly-added --ipa/--show-phonemes flags (moonshine-go: cmd/moonshine's tts.go) and cross-referencing with ../pronouncing-elvish, which already drives kokoro-cli's raw-phonemes path (-p/--phonemes) with its own hand-built Elvish G2P.

Verified this is NOT currently biting pronouncing-elvish: I checked its full char_map/diphthong_map output character set programmatically against the real ~/.local/share/kokoro/models/v1.0/tokens.txt and every character it currently emits is present. But it's a landmine for the next new digraph/IPA symbol added to any raw-phonemes consumer of kokoro-cli, in any project -- a silently-dropped character produces a plausible-sounding-but-wrong audio clip with no error to catch it.
